SIMPLE: thy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thy
<hw>Thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>thi</ets>,
shortened from <ets>thin</ets>. See <er>Thine</er>,
<er>Thou</er>.]</ety> <def>Of thee, or belonging to thee; the more
common form of <xex>thine</xex>, possessive case of <xex>thou</xex>; --
used always attributively, and chiefly in the solemn or grave style, and
in poetry. <xex>Thine</xex> is used in the predicate; <as>as, the knife
is <ex>thine</ex></as>. See <er>Thine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our father which art in heaven, Hallowed be <qex>thy</qex> name.
<qex>Thy</qex> kingdom come. <qex>Thy</qex> will be done.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. vi. 9,10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These are <qex>thy</qex> glorious works, Parent of good.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thyine wood</ent>⟦br⟧
